President Obama is set to sign the Ultralight Aircraft Smuggling Prevention Act of 2012 on Friday, February 10. This bill, which was sponsored by former Representative Gabrielle Giffords, aims to enhance law enforcement's ability to combat drug trafficking on the borders between the United States and Mexico and the United States and Canada. The bill passed unanimously in the House of Representatives and by voice vote in the Senate. President Obama will be joined by Vice President Biden, Giffords, and her husband Mark Kelly for the signing in the Oval Office. Further details will be released as they become available.